The Plateau Police Command has appointed ASP Obah Ogaba, as its new Public Relations Officer (PPRO). This is contained in a statement issued by the outgone PPRO, DSP Terna Tyopev, on Friday in Jos. Ogaba, a graduate of Physics from the University of Jos, replaces Tyopev, who has been posted to Lagos command. The statement said before his new appointment, Ogaba served as the Patrol and Guard at Nasarawa Gwong Division and had deputised Tyopev as PPRO of the commmand.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .